Plot an epiparameter distribution object

Source: R/plot_epiparameter_distribution.R
plot_epiparameter_distribution.Rd

Produces a simple plot, using base R, of an epiparameter distribution object of the class epiparameter::epidist().

Usage

plot_epiparameter_distribution(epidist, from = 0, to = 30, by = 0.1)

Arguments

epidist

An epiparameter object retrieved using the function epiparameter::epidist_db() or otherwise constructed using epiparameter::epidist()

from

The day from which to start plotting the distribution. Default option is day 0.

to

The day to which to start plotting the distribution. Default option is day 30.

by

The time resolution at which which to plot the distribution. Default option is 0.1 days.

Value

A plot of the delay distribution over time

Examples

# Retrieve the delay distribution between onset and death for Ebola,
# using the epiparameter function `epiparameter::epidist_db()`

onset_to_death_ebola <- epiparameter::epidist_db(
  disease = "Ebola Virus Disease",
  epi_dist = "onset_to_death",
  author = "Barry_etal"
)
#> Using Barry et al. (2018) <10.1016/S0140-6736(18)31387-4> PMID: 30047375. 
#> To retrieve the short citation use the 'get_citation' function

plot_epiparameter_distribution(onset_to_death_ebola, by = 1)
